---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Session Summary — SessionFS" activeNav="features" description="Automatic session summaries — files, tests, commands extracted in seconds.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative pt-32 sm:pt-40 pb-16 px-5 noise">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center gap-12">
      <div class="lg:w-1/2 fade-up">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-mono text-muted-dim mb-6">
          <a href="/features/" class="hover:text-brand transition-colors">Features</a>
          <span>&#47;</span>
          <span class="text-txt">Session Summary</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight leading-[1.1] mb-6">
          Know what happened.<br>In 10 seconds.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-muted text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">Every session automatically summarized — files changed, tests run, commands executed, key decisions made. No more reading 2,000 messages to understand what the AI did.</p>
        <p class="text-muted text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">Deterministic extraction runs instantly with no LLM cost. Parses pytest, jest, and go test output automatically.</p>
        <div class="font-mono text-sm text-accent bg-surface border border-border rounded-md p-3 inline-block mb-8">sfs summary ses_abc</div>
        <div class="block">
          <a href="/summary/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-brand text-white font-semibold rounded-lg px-6 py-3 hover:brightness-110 transition">
            Read the docs
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:w-1/2 w-full fade-up">
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="hero-glow"></div>
          <div class="term relative z-10">
            <div class="term-bar">
              <div class="term-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></div>
              <div class="term-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></div>
              <div class="term-dot bg-[#28c840]"></div>
              <span class="ml-3 text-muted-dim text-[13px] font-mono">session summary</span>
            </div>
            <div class="p-5 font-mono text-sm space-y-3">
              <div>
                <div class="text-txt font-semibold">Debug auth middleware</div>
                <div class="text-muted-dim">2.3h &middot; 327 msgs &middot; 28 tool calls</div>
                <div class="text-muted-dim">Claude Code &middot; feature/auth-fix @ a1b2c3d</div>
              </div>
              <div class="border-t border-border pt-3">
                <div class="text-muted-dim uppercase text-[11px] tracking-wider mb-1">Files</div>
                <div class="text-muted text-sm">Modified: <span class="text-txt">middleware.py, tokens.py, test_auth.py</span></div>
                <div class="text-muted text-sm">Read: <span class="text-muted-dim">config.py, user.py + 3 more</span></div>
              </div>
              <div class="border-t border-border pt-3">
                <div class="text-muted-dim uppercase text-[11px] tracking-wider mb-1">Activity</div>
                <div class="text-muted text-sm">Tests: <span class="text-accent">5 passed</span>, <span class="text-danger">1 failed</span></div>
                <div class="text-muted text-sm">Commands: 34 &middot; Packages: pyjwt, redis</div>
              </div>
              <div class="border-t border-border pt-3">
                <div class="text-muted-dim uppercase text-[11px] tracking-wider mb-1">Outcome</div>
                <div class="text-accent text-sm">Fix applied. 5/6 tests passing.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grad-divider"></div>

  <!-- Sub-feature cards -->
  <section class="relative py-20 sm:py-28 px-5 noise">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="fade-up font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-12">How summaries are built</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-5">

        <div class="glass fade-up p-6">
          <div class="mb-3"><svg class="w-7 h-7" fill="none" stroke="#f0c040" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3.75 13.5l10.5-11.25L12 10.5h8.25L9.75 21.75 12 13.5H3.75z"/></svg></div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold mb-2">No LLM needed</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-base leading-relaxed">Deterministic extraction parses tool calls directly. Files, commands, test results, packages, and errors — extracted in milliseconds, zero API cost.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass fade-up p-6">
          <div class="mb-3"><svg class="w-7 h-7" fill="none" stroke="#4f9cf7" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v6h4.5m4.5 0a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg></div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold mb-2">Test framework support</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-base leading-relaxed">Parses pytest ("5 passed, 1 failed"), jest ("Tests: 10 passed"), and go test ("ok / FAIL") output automatically — no configuration required.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass fade-up p-6">
          <div class="mb-3"><svg class="w-7 h-7" fill="none" stroke="#3ddc84" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3 13.125C3 12.504 3.504 12 4.125 12h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v6.75C7.5 20.496 6.996 21 6.375 21h-2.25A1.125 1.125 0 013 19.875v-6.75zM9.75 8.625c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v11.25c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125V8.625zM16.5 4.125c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25C20.496 3 21 3.504 21 4.125v15.75c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125V4.125z"/></svg></div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold mb-2">Dashboard + CLI</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-base leading-relaxed">Summary tab in the web dashboard with metric cards. CLI with <span class="font-mono text-accent text-sm">sfs summary --today</span> for daily overviews across all sessions.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grad-divider"></div>

  <!-- LLM narrative option -->
  <section class="relative py-20 px-5 bg-surface/50 noise">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center gap-12">
      <div class="lg:w-1/2 fade-up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Optional: LLM narrative</h2>
        <p class="text-muted text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">The deterministic layer is always free. When you want a "what happened" and "key decisions" paragraph, add your own LLM key and the summary goes narrative.</p>
        <p class="text-muted text-base mb-6 leading-relaxed">Works with the same BYOK setup as the Judge — your key, any OpenAI-compatible endpoint, never stored.</p>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Free tier: deterministic summary, always available</div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> BYOK: narrative "what happened" section</div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Pro: LLM summary on every session automatically</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:w-1/2 w-full fade-up">
        <div class="term">
          <div class="term-bar">
            <div class="term-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></div>
            <div class="term-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></div>
            <div class="term-dot bg-[#28c840]"></div>
            <span class="ml-3 text-muted-dim text-[13px] font-mono">narrative summary</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5 font-mono text-sm space-y-3">
            <div>
              <div class="text-muted-dim uppercase text-[11px] tracking-wider mb-1">What happened</div>
              <div class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Investigated JWT token expiry causing 401s on refresh. Identified the middleware was not renewing the token before expiry window. Applied fix in tokens.py. 5/6 tests now passing.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-border pt-3">
              <div class="text-muted-dim uppercase text-[11px] tracking-wider mb-1">Key decisions</div>
              <div class="text-muted text-sm">&bull; Extended expiry window from 60s to 300s</div>
              <div class="text-muted text-sm">&bull; Added redis dependency for token caching</div>
              <div class="text-muted text-sm">&bull; Deferred fixing test_auth_edge_case.py (complexity)</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grad-divider"></div>

</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(e => { if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('visible'); } });
  }, { threshold: 0.1 });
  document.querySelectorAll('.fade-up').forEach(el => observer.observe(el));
</script>
